<dl id="un1013al"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013al"> (NLI.3) 13(al)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> God of karmic law wanted to kill so Christ etc departed to the incorruptible eon <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A Study in Christian Gnosticism&rdquo; 332: &ldquo;At these things the Rulers and the Father of Jesus <font color="green">[not the Father of the Christ, but the Father of the lower Adam, the <mark>God of the K&amacr;rmic Law</mark> as opposed to the Good God of Saving Love]</font> grew angry and set to work to <mark>have him killed</mark>. <br> &nbsp; &nbsp; When this was about to be effected the <mark>Christ-together-with-Wisdom departed to the Incorruptible &AElig;on</mark>, while it was Jesus who suffered the death of crucifixion. <small> <a name="THRdec1908" href="/udra/udex.htm#thrdec1908"><cite title="source">The Theosophical Review</cite></a> (December 1908), G. R. S. Mead, &ldquo;The Secret of Jesus</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Copied to <a name="s14070ah" href="s14all.htm#s14070ah">Sheet 14.070(ah)</a> for <cite>UG</cite> 14.1169 via <a name="s14085g" href="s14all.htm#s14085g">Sheet 14.085(g)</a>, and to <a name="s14070ag" href="s14all.htm#s14070ag">Sheet 14.070(ag)</a> for <cite>UG</cite> 14.1166f via <a name="s14085h" href="s14all.htm#s14085h">Sheet 14.085(h)</a>. </mm> </dd></dl>
